steps.description:
A window will open asking where you would like to install Windows 8. In order to perform a clean install, you need to delete the old partition and start with a clean slate. Click “Drive options (advanced).” This will give you the ability to delete and create partitions. Select the partition of your existing operating system and click the Delete button. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f6/Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f6/Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you are installing an operating system for the first time on this hard drive, then there will be no partitions to delete. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/59/Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/59/Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If your hard drive has multiple partitions, be sure to delete the correct one. Any data on a deleted partition is lost for good. Confirm the deletion process. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/05/Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/05/Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-17Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

To log in to Windows, you will need an account. Microsoft recommends using a Microsoft account, so that you can make purchases in the Windows store. If you don’t have a Microsoft account, entering a valid email address will create one for free. If you don’t have an email address, click the “Sign up for a new email address” link to create one. This requires an internet connection. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/96/Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-25Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-25Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/96/Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-25Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-25Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you’d rather sign in the old way, without using a Microsoft account, click the bottom link. This will create a login similar to previous versions of Windows. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/52/Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-25Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-25Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/52/Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-25Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Install-Windows-8-from-USB-Step-25Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
